export function buildResumePrompt({
  jobDescription,
  resumeTemplate
}) {
  return `
You are an expert LaTeX editor with a deep understanding of resume formatting. Your absolute priority is to update the content of the provided LaTeX resume template to align with the job description while **STRICTLY PRESERVING ALL aspects of the original LaTeX structure and formatting.**

===========================
🛑 CRITICAL - DO NOT ALTER FORMATTING:
===========================
Under no circumstances should you modify the following:
- Any LaTeX commands (e.g., \\documentclass, \\usepackage, \\newcommand, \\begin, \\end).
- The overall document structure and section divisions (e.g., \\begin{rSection}, \\end{rSection}).
- Spacing and vertical adjustments (e.g., \\vspace, \\itemsep, \\hspace).
- Text formatting (e.g., \\textbf, \\textit, \\underline).
- List environments and their settings (e.g., \\begin{itemize}, \\end{itemize}, [leftmargin=*]).
- Table environments and their structure (e.g., \\begin{tabular}, \\end{tabular}, column specifications).
- Any special LaTeX characters or symbols.

Your sole task is to **replace the text content** within specific sections as instructed below, ensuring that the surrounding LaTeX code remains **EXACTLY THE SAME**.

===========================
🎯 GOAL:
===========================
Adapt the resume content to highlight relevant skills and experiences from the job description, without introducing any formatting errors.

===========================
📝 INSTRUCTIONS:
===========================

1. **Summary Section (\\begin{rSection}{Summary}):**
   - **Keep the FIRST bullet point UNCHANGED.**
   - **Carefully rewrite the content ONLY** of the **SECOND** and **THIRD** bullet points to reflect key skills and experiences mentioned in the job description. Ensure each new bullet point starts with \\item.

2. **Experience Section (\\begin{rSection}{Experience}):**
   - Locate the "**Software Engineer | MetLife**" and "**Software Engineer | Adons Soft Tech**" entries.
   - For **MetLife**, **rewrite the content ONLY** of **ALL** existing \\item bullet points to align with the job description.
   - For **Adons Soft Tech**, **rewrite the content ONLY** of **ALL** existing \\item bullet points to align with the job description.
   - **DO NOT modify** the bullet points for "**Software Engineer (Java) | Nagarro Software Limited**" or "**Nithya Industries (Startup)**".

3. **Technical Skills Section (\\begin{rSection}{Technical Skills}):**
   - Review the job description for relevant technical skills.
   - **Modify the text content ONLY** within the \\begin{tabular} environment to emphasize these skills. You can replace existing skills with more relevant ones, or reorder them. **Do not add or remove rows or columns.** Ensure the & and \\ separators remain untouched.

===========================
🔍 JOB DESCRIPTION:
===========================
${jobDescription}

===========================
📄 LATEX TEMPLATE:
===========================
${resumeTemplate}

===========================
✅ OUTPUT FORMAT:
===========================
Return a JSON object with the following format:

\`\`\`json
{
  "updatedLatex": "FULL UPDATED LATEX CODE HERE",
  "changesSummary": [
    "Rewrote content of the 2nd and 3rd bullet points in the Summary section.",
    "Rewrote content of bullet points in the MetLife experience section.",
    "Rewrote content of bullet points in the Adons Soft Tech experience section.",
    "Modified text content within the Technical Skills table."
  ]
}
\`\`\`
`;
}
